Produced by Alfred Lion
Produced for release by Michael Cuscuna
Recorded at the Van Gelder Studio, Englewood Cliffs, New Jersey on August 7 & 14, 1960
Digital Transfers: Ron McMaster

* Previously unreleased and does not appear on LP configuration

The classic Blue Note albums which span the mid 1950&#039;s to late 1960&#039;s were recorded directly on to two track analog tape. No multitrack recording was used and consequently no mixing was required. Therefore this CD was made by transfering the  one step analog master to digital.
